    GPA species information

    GPA.Rd

    A species object defining the life history and function for green peach aphid (Myzus persicae). Can be used to run the endosymbiont model on GPA.

    f_growth fitted using fit_custom with data from Whalon & Smilowitz 1979.
    f_loss fitted using fit_sigmoid with data from Maling et al. 2008.
    f_suscept fitted using fit_custom with data from Thackray et al. 2009.
    f_inoc fitted using fit_quadratic with data from Thackray et al. 2009.
    f_alate fitted using fit_custom with data from Thackray et al. 2009.

    Usage

    data(GPA)

    Format

    An object of class species; see species.

    References

    Maling, T., Diggle, A.J., Thackray, D.J., Siddique, K.H.M., Jones, R.A.C., An epidemiological model for externally sourced vector-borne viruses applied to Bean yellow mosaic virus in lupin crops in a Mediterranean-type environment. Phytopathology, 98, 1280–1290 (2008)

    Thackray, D.J., Diggle, A.J., Jones, R.A.C., BYDV PREDICTOR: a simulation model to predict aphid arrival, epidemics of Barley yellow dwarf virus and yield loss in wheat crops in a Mediterranean-type environment. Plant Pathology, 58, 186–202 (2009)]

    Whalon, M.E., Smilowitz, Z., Temperature-dependent model for predicting field populations of green peach aphid, Myzus persicae. The Canadian Entomologist, 111, 1025–1032 (1979)
